      "created_at": "2026-05-07T15:27:50.000Z",
      "text": "@woisau1 We use rolling context files across 12+ agents in production. The hard part is selective forgetting. Cross-agent memory bleed killed us early - one agent's stale context poisoned another's decisions. Explicit decay policies per agent type fixed it.",
